a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes z :: complex
assumes h0 : "z = Complex (Re (1/2)) (Im (-3/8))"
shows  "cmod z = 5 / 8"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Evaluate $\left|\frac12 - \frac38i\right|$. The final Answer is \frac58
 ### Proof
 We have \[\left|\frac12 - \frac38i\right| = \left|\frac{1}{8}\left(4 - 3i\right)\right| = \frac18|4-3i| = \frac18\sqrt{4^2 +(-3)^2} = \boxed{\frac58}.\]
 *)

theorem
fixes z :: complex
assumes h0 : "z = Complex (Re (1/2)) (Im (-3/8))"
shows  "cmod z = 5 / 8"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Find the absolute value or modulus of the complex number $(1/2) - 3i/8$. The final answer is $5/8$.
